<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1437,1302,1653]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[562,708,1302,1329]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Pacific Hake</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[754,842,1303,1329]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.14" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="cm" value="91.4">91.4 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[855,911,1303,1330]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.144" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="in" value="36.0">36 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" box="[970,1196,1303,1329]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Attu Island, Aleutian Islands (one record), eastern Bering Sea (
<geoCoordinate box="[670,768,1338,1365]" degrees="54" direction="north" minutes="43" orientation="latitude" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" precision="925" value="54.716667">54°43’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[783,901,1338,1365]" degrees="165" direction="west" minutes="42" orientation="longitude" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" precision="925" value="-165.7">165°42’W</geoCoordinate>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Maslenikov" box="[928,1201,1339,1365]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Maslenikov" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref299182" refString="Maslenikov, K. P., Orr, J. W. &amp; Stevenson, D. W. (2013) Range extensions and significant distributional records for eighty-two species of fishes in Alaskan marine waters. Northwestern Naturalist, 94, 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.1898 / 12 - 23.1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Maslenikov 
<emphasis box="[1072,1132,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and Gulf of Alaska (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[360,416,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
2002) to Bahía 
<collectingRegion box="[595,719,1375,1401]" country="Colombia" name="Magdalena" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Magdalena</collectingRegion>
, southern Baja California and Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller and Lea" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[299,406,1411,1437]" name="Colombia" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(Cohen in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cohen" box="[530,728,1411,1437]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cohen" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refId="ref271020" refString="Cohen, D. M., Inada, T., Iwamoto, T. &amp; Scialabba, N. (1990) FAO Species Catalogue. Gadiform Fishes of the World. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, Volume 10. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1990">
Cohen 
<emphasis box="[609,664,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
), and Islas Revillagigedo (
<bibRefCitation author="Robertson and Allen" box="[1021,1317,1411,1437]" firstAuthor="Robertson" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refId="ref316751" refString="Robertson, D. R. &amp; Allen, G. R. (2008) Shorefishes of the Tropical Eastern Pacific: an Information System. Version 1.0 (2008). Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute, Balboa." type="book" year="2008">Robertson and Allen 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Reported from continental slope of Bering Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Fedorov" box="[605,761,1447,1473]" firstAuthor="Fedorov" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="3 - 41" refId="ref278395" refString="Fedorov, V. V. (1973) Ichthyofauna of the continental slope of the Bering Sea and some aspects of its origin and development. Izvestija TINRO, 87, 3 - 41. [Fisheries Marine Service Translation Series No. 3345. Department of the Environment, Fisheries and Marine Service, Pacific Biological Station, Nanaimo, B. C., Canada.]" type="journal article" year="1973">Fedorov 1973</bibRefCitation>
), but vouchers are needed to confirm continued existence there (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[358,413,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
2002). Oceanic and neritic pelagic (Inada in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cohen" box="[899,1096,1483,1509]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Cohen" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refId="ref271020" refString="Cohen, D. M., Inada, T., Iwamoto, T. &amp; Scialabba, N. (1990) FAO Species Catalogue. Gadiform Fishes of the World. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, Volume 10. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1990">
Cohen 
<emphasis box="[977,1031,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
); depth: 
<quantity box="[1188,1318,1483,1509]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.245" metricValueMax="14.37" metricValueMin="0.12" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="m" value="724.5" valueMax="1437.0" valueMin="12.0">12–1,437 m</quantity>
(
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.242048" metricValueMax="14.365224" metricValueMin="0.118872" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="ft" value="2376.0" valueMax="4713.0" valueMin="39.0">39–4,713 ft</quantity>
) (min.: M.L., unpubl. data; max.: DFO). We also note that there is a much deeper record of 
<quantity box="[1232,1324,1518,1545]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.857" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="m" value="1857.0">1,857 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1338,1429,1519,1546]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8565368" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="ft" value="6091.0">6,091 ft</quantity>
) (DFO) from a bottom trawl haul. Given that this species may occur well off the bottom, this latter catch may have occurred as the trawl was deployed or retrieved. We consider 
<taxonomicName authority="Garman, 1899" authorityName="Garman" authorityYear="1899" box="[936,1377,1591,1617]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Merlucciidae" genus="Merluccius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angustimanus">
<emphasis box="[936,1216,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Merluccius angustimanus</emphasis>
Garman, 1899
</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym (
<bibRefCitation author="Silva-Segundo" box="[331,618,1627,1653]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Silva-Segundo" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" pagination="259 - 282" refId="ref322801" refString="Silva-Segundo, C. A., Brito-Chavarria, M., Balart, E. F., de los A. Barriga-Sosa, I., Rojas-Esquivel, R., Roldan, M. I., Murugan, G. &amp; Garcia-De Leon, F. J. (2011) Clarifying the taxonomic status of Merluccius spp. in the northeastern Pacific: a combined morphological and molecular approach. Reviews of Fish Biology and Fisheries, 21, 259 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11160 - 010 - 9166 - 6" type="journal article" year="2011">
Silva-Segundo 
<emphasis box="[500,555,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
